WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.546 --> 00:00:05.713
(humming)

2
00:00:43.543 --> 00:00:45.961
(bird caws)

3
00:00:45.961 --> 00:00:49.044
(suspenseful music)

4
00:00:55.613 --> 00:00:58.196
- Our father who art in heaven,

5
00:00:59.148 --> 00:01:01.981
hallowed be thy name, thy kingdom,

6
00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:06.760
thy kingdom come, thy will be done.

7
00:01:12.740 --> 00:01:15.323
(wind howling)

8
00:01:49.686 --> 00:01:51.436
I can't feel my feet.

9
00:01:52.706 --> 00:01:54.039
Oh it's so cold.

10
00:01:56.633 --> 00:01:58.883
(groaning)

11
00:02:00.674 --> 00:02:02.841
(sobbing)

12
00:02:14.980 --> 00:02:16.837
God, help me.

13
00:02:16.837 --> 00:02:20.087
I'll never get there without a lantern.

14
00:02:21.395 --> 00:02:22.895
Are you there God?

15
00:02:24.067 --> 00:02:25.234
Are you there?

16
00:02:27.022 --> 00:02:28.772
Do you care about me?

17
00:02:29.996 --> 00:02:32.996
(suspenseful music)

18
00:02:39.675 --> 00:02:40.508
Oh, God.

19
00:02:41.376 --> 00:02:44.343
You helped Annette, when
she was stuck in the snow.

20
00:02:45.666 --> 00:02:47.330
Help me, please.

21
00:02:50.288 --> 00:02:51.121
Please.

22
00:02:53.863 --> 00:02:57.499
I didn't do that to Dani on purpose.

23
00:02:57.499 --> 00:02:59.082
I promise I didn't.

24
00:03:00.195 --> 00:03:02.635
Please help me.

25
00:03:02.635 --> 00:03:05.560
Please help me to get to the doctor.

26
00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:08.560
Please help me to get to the doctor.

27
00:03:10.036 --> 00:03:10.869
Please.

28
00:03:21.596 --> 00:03:24.263
Please someone come and find me.

29
00:03:43.178 --> 00:03:45.928
(peaceful music)

30
00:03:55.776 --> 00:03:58.443
(door knocking)

31
00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:05.333
- Yes?

32
00:04:05.333 --> 00:04:07.140
- Excuse me Monsieur Givert,

33
00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:09.823
where you by any chance
expecting any, any visitors?

34
00:04:11.014 --> 00:04:14.728
- A visitor, at this hour?

35
00:04:14.728 --> 00:04:17.130
- Yes, it's like this Monsieur.

36
00:04:17.130 --> 00:04:19.060
About quarter of an hour ago,

37
00:04:19.060 --> 00:04:20.550
I heard a little rap on the door

38
00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:21.920
and when I went to answer it,

39
00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:24.770
there standing on the
step is this boy in skis.

40
00:04:24.770 --> 00:04:27.630
About 12 years old, white as a sheet,

41
00:04:27.630 --> 00:04:29.438
looking more like a ghost than a boy.

42
00:04:29.438 --> 00:04:30.271
(laughs)

43
00:04:30.271 --> 00:04:32.650
"I want to see Monsieur Givert" says he.

44
00:04:32.650 --> 00:04:34.190
Without so much as a good morning.

45
00:04:34.190 --> 00:04:35.630
Then he falls down on his knees

46
00:04:35.630 --> 00:04:37.457
and leans his head against the door post.

47
00:04:37.457 --> 00:04:39.637
"Well" says I, "you can't
come calling on people

48
00:04:39.637 --> 00:04:42.877
"at this time in the morning,
he's sound asleep in his bed."

49
00:04:42.877 --> 00:04:45.110
"Then I'll wait" says he.

50
00:04:45.110 --> 00:04:47.550
And he sinks his head down in his knees.

51
00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:50.270
Well sir, I don't like
to see a child like that.

52
00:04:50.270 --> 00:04:52.890
So I takes his skis off,
and I drags him inside

53
00:04:52.890 --> 00:04:54.447
and I puts him on a chair.

54
00:04:54.447 --> 00:04:56.647
"Where have you come from?" says I.

55
00:04:56.647 --> 00:04:58.587
"From Pays-d'Enhaut" says he.

56
00:04:58.587 --> 00:05:01.527
"Hows that?" says I, "the
early train's not in yet."

57
00:05:01.527 --> 00:05:04.843
"I came through the pass" says he.

58
00:05:04.843 --> 00:05:06.473
Yes Monsieur, through the pass.

59
00:05:07.650 --> 00:05:09.510
And the more I look at him,

60
00:05:09.510 --> 00:05:11.563
the more likely I feel to believe it.

61
00:05:12.450 --> 00:05:13.520
And when I saw your light on

62
00:05:13.520 --> 00:05:15.553
I thought I'd come and see
if you'd like to see him too.

63
00:05:16.730 --> 00:05:19.400
- Well, I'll come and see him certainly.

64
00:05:19.400 --> 00:05:20.930
But as for coming through the pass

65
00:05:20.930 --> 00:05:22.100
I don't believe a word of it.

66
00:05:22.100 --> 00:05:23.693
It must have been terrible
out there last night.

67
00:05:23.693 --> 00:05:25.533
- Well you'll see for yourself sir.

68
00:05:34.502 --> 00:05:35.335
- Oh dear.

69
00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:42.380
(suspenseful music)

70
00:05:47.360 --> 00:05:48.610
I'll take him to my room.

71
00:05:51.170 --> 00:05:54.710
Bring me a hot water
bottle and some brandy.

72
00:05:54.710 --> 00:05:57.420
Oh and some hot coffee.

73
00:05:57.420 --> 00:05:58.476
- Yes sir.

74
00:05:58.476 --> 00:05:59.309
- And be as quick as you can.

75
00:05:59.309 --> 00:06:00.476
- At once sir.

76
00:06:09.510 --> 00:06:10.427
- Ah right.

77
00:06:22.515 --> 00:06:23.348
- Monsieur.

78
00:06:23.348 --> 00:06:24.181
- Ah.

79
00:06:24.181 --> 00:06:25.014
- A hot water bottle.

80
00:06:25.014 --> 00:06:26.240
- Thank you Porter.

81
00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:29.426
- And uh, Brandy Monsieur.

82
00:06:29.426 --> 00:06:31.128
- Thank you.

83
00:06:31.128 --> 00:06:33.850
- Oh, the poor boy.

84
00:06:33.850 --> 00:06:35.200
Yes.

85
00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:36.060
- Thank you.

86
00:06:36.060 --> 00:06:37.867
- I'll get the coffee Monsieur.

87
00:06:43.884 --> 00:06:45.134
- That's right.

88
00:06:47.052 --> 00:06:50.052
(suspenseful music)

89
00:07:10.631 --> 00:07:11.798
- Who are you?

90
00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:20.100
- I'm Monsieur Givert, I
understand you wanted to see me.

91
00:07:24.668 --> 00:07:26.963
- Are you the great,
clever, famous doctor?

92
00:07:28.618 --> 00:07:30.853
- (laughs) No, I'm just a doctor.

93
00:07:34.490 --> 00:07:37.157
- Can you make lame children walk?

94
00:07:38.440 --> 00:07:42.023
- It depends why they're
lame, sometimes I can.

95
00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:46.340
- He fell off a precipice

96
00:07:47.340 --> 00:07:49.510
and now he has to walk with crutches.

97
00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:50.343
- Who?

98
00:07:52.324 --> 00:07:54.210
- Little Dani Burnier.

99
00:07:54.210 --> 00:07:56.010
He lives in the chalet next to ours.

100
00:07:58.638 --> 00:08:02.240
I was going to ask whether
you could make him well again.

101
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:03.270
- Coffee Monsieur.

102
00:08:03.270 --> 00:08:04.550
- Thank you Porter.

103
00:08:06.718 --> 00:08:08.016
- Here we are.

104
00:08:08.016 --> 00:08:09.266
- There we are.

105
00:08:10.445 --> 00:08:11.278
Here hmm.

106
00:08:15.800 --> 00:08:17.370
How did you hear of me?

107
00:08:20.037 --> 00:08:23.287
- My sister's a maid here, she told me.

108
00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:31.383
- But how did you get here in that storm?

109
00:08:32.439 --> 00:08:34.433
- I came over the pass on my skis.

110
00:08:36.100 --> 00:08:40.483
- (laughs) You couldn't
have done, not that night.

111
00:08:42.150 --> 00:08:42.983
- But I did.

112
00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:54.903
Please sir, would this be
enough to make Dani better?

113
00:09:03.802 --> 00:09:06.030
(bell ringing)

114
00:09:06.030 --> 00:09:07.123
- Excuse me, sir.

115
00:09:11.100 --> 00:09:12.750
- What's your name?

116
00:09:12.750 --> 00:09:14.233
- Lucien Morell.

117
00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:17.750
- Lucien, bfore we go any further

118
00:09:17.750 --> 00:09:20.093
I must know where this money came from.

119
00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:23.470
Do you know how much there is here?

120
00:09:23.470 --> 00:09:27.670
- No, but my sister said you'd want a lot.

121
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:29.259
Isn't it enough?

122
00:09:29.259 --> 00:09:31.220
- (laughs) That depends whether

123
00:09:31.220 --> 00:09:33.173
you want to buy my clinic as well.

124
00:09:34.960 --> 00:09:37.233
Lucien, where did you get it?

125
00:09:39.696 --> 00:09:42.740
- An old man I know, I'm friends with him.

126
00:09:42.740 --> 00:09:44.733
And there's a message with it he said.

127
00:09:46.136 --> 00:09:50.007
It was a payment of a debt
and you are to take it all.

128
00:09:51.180 --> 00:09:52.777
- Who is this old man?

129
00:09:52.777 --> 00:09:54.183
What's his name?

130
00:09:54.183 --> 00:09:55.253
- I don't know.

131
00:09:56.710 --> 00:09:57.760
- Where does he live?

132
00:10:00.230 --> 00:10:03.043
- Please, he made me
promise not to tell you.

133
00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:10.550
He's sort of a secret and no
one goes to see him except me.

134
00:10:17.097 --> 00:10:20.593
- All right, I shan't ask
anything more for now.

135
00:10:23.300 --> 00:10:25.623
But tell me about little Dani's accident.

136
00:10:26.800 --> 00:10:28.973
How did it happen and when?

137
00:10:32.694 --> 00:10:33.944
- It was my fault really.

138
00:10:35.580 --> 00:10:39.092
I was teasing him and then,

139
00:10:39.092 --> 00:10:42.883
I pretended to drop to
drop his cat over a ravine.

140
00:10:43.820 --> 00:10:46.363
And then by mistake, I really did.

141
00:10:48.140 --> 00:10:51.840
Dani went after it,
fell and broke his leg.

142
00:10:51.840 --> 00:10:55.790
And ever since, he's never
walked properly again.

143
00:10:55.790 --> 00:10:57.130
And I thought perhaps--

144
00:10:57.130 --> 00:10:58.033
- All right.

145
00:10:59.810 --> 00:11:01.360
We'll go and see Dani together.

146
00:11:02.515 --> 00:11:05.210
It may be that God is going to make you

147
00:11:05.210 --> 00:11:06.737
the means of curing him.

148
00:11:09.180 --> 00:11:12.463
You know, you have a lot to thank God for.

149
00:11:14.290 --> 00:11:16.140
I think he must have
been looking after you

150
00:11:16.140 --> 00:11:19.080
in a very special way last night,

151
00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:21.530
or you would never have
got over that pass alone.

152
00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:25.993
Now, I think you'd better get some sleep.

153
00:11:25.993 --> 00:11:27.130
(door knocking)

154
00:11:27.130 --> 00:11:28.857
Before I take you home, hm?

155
00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:38.867
- Porter Monsieur Givert,
ah, Monsieur Givert!

156
00:11:38.867 --> 00:11:40.737
- Oh sir, Porter tells me
you've got my little brother.

157
00:11:40.737 --> 00:11:42.140
Is he all right?

158
00:11:42.140 --> 00:11:44.514
- Yes, exhausted but all right.

159
00:11:44.514 --> 00:11:47.180
- Oh sir, we've been
searching for him all night.

160
00:11:47.180 --> 00:11:50.000
- Don't worry my dear, I
think he'll be all right now.

161
00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:51.670
Perhaps you'd tell Dani's parents

162
00:11:51.670 --> 00:11:53.750
that I'll be along to see him, would you?

163
00:11:53.750 --> 00:11:54.760
- Yes, thank you Monsieur.

164
00:11:54.760 --> 00:11:56.620
- Thank you so much, you're
very helpful, thank you.

165
00:11:56.620 --> 00:11:58.140
- Porter I'll certain the management

166
00:11:58.140 --> 00:11:59.586
will give you the day off.

167
00:11:59.586 --> 00:12:01.939
- Dr. Givert I'm sure they will.

168
00:12:01.939 --> 00:12:04.522
(bell ringing)

169
00:12:38.879 --> 00:12:41.712
(cheerful music)

170
00:12:44.894 --> 00:12:46.977
(coughs)

171
00:13:19.576 --> 00:13:22.159
- Dani, would you like a sweet?

172
00:13:26.565 --> 00:13:27.648
- Yes, go on.

173
00:13:34.448 --> 00:13:38.684
- (laughs) Does your leg hurt you?

174
00:13:38.684 --> 00:13:39.869
- No.

175
00:13:39.869 --> 00:13:40.724
- Hmm.

176
00:13:40.724 --> 00:13:41.891
- No Monsieur.

177
00:13:42.994 --> 00:13:43.911
- Monsieur.

178
00:13:46.034 --> 00:13:49.800
Only sometimes when I
walk without my crutches.

179
00:13:49.800 --> 00:13:51.480
Would you like to see my crutches?

180
00:13:51.480 --> 00:13:53.013
- Very much indeed.

181
00:14:04.316 --> 00:14:08.390
- Ah, (laughs) wonderful.

182
00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:09.793
Just like a kangaroo.

183
00:14:11.240 --> 00:14:13.180
Now give me your crutches

184
00:14:13.180 --> 00:14:15.773
and let me see you walk without them, hm?

185
00:14:18.246 --> 00:14:20.996
(peaceful music)

186
00:14:36.554 --> 00:14:38.971
Ah (laughs).

187
00:14:40.635 --> 00:14:42.300
- Lets have some coffee, shall we Annette?

188
00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:43.203
- Yes Grandma.

189
00:14:47.788 --> 00:14:51.788
- There we go

190
00:14:51.788 --> 00:14:52.621
Now.

191
00:14:53.879 --> 00:14:54.712
Hmm, now.

192
00:14:56.978 --> 00:14:57.811
Hmm-mm.

193
00:14:59.510 --> 00:15:00.343
Hmm-mm.

194
00:15:01.633 --> 00:15:04.440
Yeah, yes.

195
00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:06.533
- Well?

196
00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:11.150
- Would you like to be able to run around

197
00:15:11.150 --> 00:15:13.010
like other little boys, hmm?

198
00:15:20.210 --> 00:15:21.043
- Hmm-mm.

199
00:15:22.320 --> 00:15:25.013
- Dani, where's that fine cat gone?

200
00:15:26.500 --> 00:15:29.270
- To the woodshed, would
you like to see him?

201
00:15:29.270 --> 00:15:30.293
- Yes please.

202
00:15:32.219 --> 00:15:33.052
Whey.

203
00:15:40.022 --> 00:15:42.920
I think I may be able to help you,

204
00:15:42.920 --> 00:15:45.053
though I'd have to see the X-Rays first.

205
00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:48.374
I think the bone was not properly set

206
00:15:48.374 --> 00:15:51.427
and has joined up in the wrong way.

207
00:15:51.427 --> 00:15:55.798
I could break it again
and pull it out straight,

208
00:15:55.798 --> 00:15:59.803
but it would mean an operation
and a long stay in hospital.

209
00:16:01.220 --> 00:16:03.063
Would you be willing to let him come?

210
00:16:05.550 --> 00:16:08.233
- Well, um, how much would it cost?

211
00:16:09.360 --> 00:16:12.933
- It wouldn't cost you
anything, Lucien has paid.

212
00:16:14.740 --> 00:16:16.220
But I can't explain that now,

213
00:16:16.220 --> 00:16:18.333
we must decide before Dani comes back.

214
00:16:19.370 --> 00:16:20.620
Will you let me take him?

215
00:16:28.030 --> 00:16:29.369
- Yes.

216
00:16:29.369 --> 00:16:30.202
- When?

217
00:16:30.202 --> 00:16:33.520
- Tomorrow, I'll be
leaving on the early train,

218
00:16:33.520 --> 00:16:34.733
I'll take Dani with me.

219
00:16:35.617 --> 00:16:37.177
- On the train?

220
00:16:37.177 --> 00:16:38.594
Where am I going?

221
00:16:42.694 --> 00:16:43.900
Where Annette?

222
00:16:43.900 --> 00:16:46.560
- Dani, you're coming
with me down to the lake,

223
00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:48.957
where I'm going to make your leg better.

224
00:16:48.957 --> 00:16:52.393
- And Annette, and Klaus,
and Grandma and Papa.

225
00:16:53.579 --> 00:16:55.283
- Oh, Dani we can't all come.

226
00:17:01.110 --> 00:17:04.830
- Does the girl know anything
about looking after children?

227
00:17:04.830 --> 00:17:06.130
- She brought this one up.

228
00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:10.513
- And Annette.

229
00:17:14.060 --> 00:17:17.310
So, I want to see you two at the station

230
00:17:17.310 --> 00:17:19.570
at half past eight tomorrow
morning and enough things

231
00:17:19.570 --> 00:17:22.010
to last you for two or
three months, all right?

232
00:17:22.010 --> 00:17:22.843
- Yes.

233
00:17:24.987 --> 00:17:28.360
- Now, I must take poor Lucien home.

234
00:17:29.792 --> 00:17:34.036
And then I have another
small matter to deal with.

235
00:17:34.036 --> 00:17:36.703
(bells ringing)

236
00:17:55.944 --> 00:17:57.611
Who's that old man?

237
00:17:59.855 --> 00:18:00.688
Oi, stop.

238
00:18:04.120 --> 00:18:04.963
Do you know him?

239
00:18:12.390 --> 00:18:13.223
The money.

240
00:18:19.327 --> 00:18:20.994
Excuse me, Monsieur!

241
00:18:21.967 --> 00:18:23.634
Excuse me, Monsieur!

242
00:18:24.599 --> 00:18:25.432
Monsieur!

243
00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:27.944
Excuse me, Monsieur.

244
00:18:27.944 --> 00:18:31.073
Excuse me, Monsieur, I know
this sounds rather silly

245
00:18:31.073 --> 00:18:33.120
but this sock, do you know
anything about this sock?

246
00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:34.226
- No, no no, no.

247
00:18:34.226 --> 00:18:35.389
- And that little boy down there?

248
00:18:35.389 --> 00:18:36.598
- No, no, no.

249
00:18:36.598 --> 00:18:38.098
- Please Monsieur.

250
00:18:43.323 --> 00:18:45.032
No it can't be.

251
00:18:45.032 --> 00:18:47.365
(laughing)

252
00:18:57.260 --> 00:18:58.253
Come with me.

253
00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:01.015
Oh where have you been?

254
00:19:01.015 --> 00:19:02.111
- Oh, such a long time.

255
00:19:02.111 --> 00:19:03.362
- What have you been doing?

256
00:19:03.362 --> 00:19:05.014
Why didn't you get in touch with me?

257
00:19:05.014 --> 00:19:06.150
- I've been so ashamed.

258
00:19:06.150 --> 00:19:07.500
- But you might have known,

259
00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:09.596
we've been wondering where you were.

260
00:19:09.596 --> 00:19:12.083
- Woodcarver It would
have spoiled your life.

261
00:19:12.083 --> 00:19:13.099
- Dr. Givert But why did you go away?

262
00:19:13.099 --> 00:19:13.932
- Woodcarver It would have
spoiled all your chances.

263
00:19:13.932 --> 00:19:15.859
- Dr. Givert Oh no, no.

264
00:19:15.859 --> 00:19:16.926
- It would have.

265
00:19:16.926 --> 00:19:17.759
(laughing)

266
00:19:17.759 --> 00:19:19.680
Oh it's so good to see you my boy.

267
00:19:19.680 --> 00:19:20.513
So good.

268
00:19:20.513 --> 00:19:23.883
- Lucien, I would like
you to meet my father.

269
00:19:25.260 --> 00:19:27.522
He's coming home with me as well.

270
00:19:27.522 --> 00:19:30.160
(laughing)

271
00:19:30.160 --> 00:19:32.393
Come on father, get on the sleigh.

272
00:19:35.084 --> 00:19:37.167
There we are, what a day.

273
00:19:38.654 --> 00:19:41.987
(laughs) Lets go, away.

274
00:19:43.185 --> 00:19:45.935
(cheerful music)

275
00:20:22.233 --> 00:20:24.779
- Hello Lucien, where are you going?

276
00:20:24.779 --> 00:20:25.812
- I'm going to the station,

277
00:20:25.812 --> 00:20:27.278
Annette and Dani are coming today.

278
00:20:27.278 --> 00:20:28.859
- Oh, give them my love.

279
00:20:28.859 --> 00:20:29.695
- All right.

280
00:20:29.695 --> 00:20:30.528
- Hello Lucien.

281
00:20:30.528 --> 00:20:31.778
- Good morning.

282
00:20:33.923 --> 00:20:36.447
- Grandma Burnier Do you
think they will have changed?

283
00:20:36.447 --> 00:20:38.408
- Monsieur Burnier Oh mother,
surely not in three months.

284
00:20:38.408 --> 00:20:40.050
- Grandma Burnier My dear
when you were their age.

285
00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:41.237
- Monsieur Burnier Yes I know.

286
00:20:41.237 --> 00:20:42.740
And they were dragged off to the city

287
00:20:42.740 --> 00:20:44.380
by some stranger as well.

288
00:20:46.270 --> 00:20:48.972
- The place has been
so quiet without them.

289
00:20:48.972 --> 00:20:50.722
- Yes, it has rather.

290
00:20:52.412 --> 00:20:55.579
(train horn whistles)

291
00:21:00.637 --> 00:21:03.387
(train rattling)

292
00:21:12.380 --> 00:21:14.130
Can you see them yet?

293
00:21:16.162 --> 00:21:17.253
- Lucien Voiceover It was your fault.

294
00:21:17.253 --> 00:21:19.093
it was all your fault.

295
00:21:22.820 --> 00:21:23.653
- There they are.

296
00:21:23.653 --> 00:21:24.486
Look, can you see them?

297
00:21:24.486 --> 00:21:25.319
- Yes.

298
00:21:28.083 --> 00:21:29.341
- Annette Voiceover It was your fault.

299
00:21:29.341 --> 00:21:31.174
It was all your fault.

300
00:21:33.097 --> 00:21:33.930
- Hello.

301
00:21:36.386 --> 00:21:37.969
Come on, come here.

302
00:21:40.040 --> 00:21:40.873
- Dr. Givert Voiceover Maybe that God

303
00:21:40.873 --> 00:21:43.223
